            <div id="myHeader" style="background-color: #fed780;padding: 20px;margin: 10px;">
              <h1 style="color: #3D5161;margin-top: 0px;font-family: Tahoma;">News</h1>
              <p style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;">It has been a typical heads down kind of January on the social front but thankfully there were lots of great stories and reporting going on.
It was great to see a packed newsroom in the Belfast office when Irish Mirror production staff had a new year meet-up. Some people met for the first time in a long time and some for the first time ever! And we are looking forward to more of the same in 2023. A similar get together for Irish Daily Star production as well as news and reporting colleagues in Dublin will hopefully happen in the brand new Talbot Street office sometime in February. January also saw some great stories and journalism that got the year off to a good start. Some highlights included Paul Healy and Michael O’Toole’s coverage of the Gerry Hutch trial which won over a new audience of listeners to the Star’s Shattered Lives podcast. John Hand who from day one has done the best reporting on one of the big early stories of the year, the sad story of little Alejandro Mizsan who was horrifically attacked by a dog. And Louise Burne who broke new ground on the story of Pascal Donohoe’s election expenses.Finally we would like to wish everyone well with the imminent launch of the irishstar.com website in the US, and especially Laura Colgan and Katie Gallagher who hope to be heading stateside soon to be part of this exciting new chapter. Best of luck!
</p>
              

            </div>
