          <div id="Circulation">
            <div id="myHeader" style="background-color: #fed780;padding: 20px;margin: 10px;">
              <h1 style="color: #3D5161;margin-top: 0px;font-family: Tahoma;">Circulation</h1>
              <p style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;">The December issue of RSVP sold 20,322 (8% YoY), whilst the RSVP Country Special which went out at the end of November sold 12,418, which is a good number in a very challenging magazine market due to the cost of living crisis. Our Slimming World magazines at the start of January supported by TV and radio delivered some significant sales increases across the Irish Daily Mirror (10%), Irish Sunday Mirror (7%), Daily Mirror (5%), Sunday Mirror (4%) and Irish Daily Star (4%), and has given us a really positive start to the year - ensuring that all titles should finish ahead of the budget forecast for the month of January. Onwards and Upwards!
</p>             
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="Digital">
            <div id="myHeader" style="background-color: #fed780;padding: 20px;margin: 10px;">
              <h1 style="color: #3D5161;margin-top: 0px;font-family: Tahoma;">Digital</h1>
              <p style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;">It's been a busy start to the year with lots of comings and goings. Good luck to Rachel Curran, who is now on maternity leave awaiting baby number two. Mark O'Brien is captain of the Dublin Live ship in her absence. Kayla Walsh has also left a big hole in the RSVP team as she embarks on an adventure of a lifetime to Australia, while Ryan Smith is the first member of the <a href="https://www.irishstar.com/" style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;"><b>IrishStar.com</b></a> team to jet off to New York ahead of its launch. Welcome back to Blathin DePaor, who has just returned to RSVP from maternity leave. Cian O'Broin has joined the Irish Mirror team from the Limerick Leader, while Darragh Murphy has also moved to the site after a successful stint as Editor of<a href="https://www.buzz.ie/" style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;"><b>Buzz.ie</b></a> . Finally, congratulations to John O'Sullivan on his engagement to partner Robynn.
