          <div id="Inclusion">
            <div id="myHeader" style="background-color: #fed780;padding: 20px;margin: 10px;">
              <h1 style="color: #3D5161;margin-top: 0px;font-family: Tahoma;">Inclusion</h1>
              <p style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;"> It's important that we all play our part in bringing inclusion to life at Reach. If you’re passionate about increasing the understanding of D&I issues we want to hear from you. We are growing our inclusion network and we’d love you to be part of this. Using the feedback from the D&I surveys we’ve identified four key events we want to roll out next year and we need your help. 
For more information contact <a href="reachirelandinclusionchampions@reachplc.com" style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;"><b>reachirelandinclusionchampions@reachplc.com</b></a>


We also want to shine a spotlight on the importance of looking after your health - both mental and physical. Reach colleagues all have access to My Healthy Advantage app which includes access to live chat with qualified counsellors or advisors 24/7, Mini health checks to help you manage your sleep, alcohol intake, BMI and much more. 


We also have two qualified mental health first aiders in Ireland -
Laura Hennessy & Jenny Murray who are always available  if anyone ever needs to talk in confidence. Remember help is always available. For more information please click <a href="https://sites.google.com/reachplc" style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;"><b>here</b></a> and for external support please click <a href="https://www.mentalhealthireland.ie/get-support/?external=1c" style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;"><b>here</b></a>. 
